  "target_response": {
    "text": "Yes — that's a sensible plan. Going from 73.5 kg to the 71 kg class is a modest total, and 0.5 kg a week is within the range generally considered sustainable at your size, slow enough to protect strength and training quality. Two things will keep it on track: anchor protein at every meal so the loss comes mostly from fat, and judge the scale by its weekly trend, not the daily wobble. Aim to sit at the limit with a week or more to spare, so you're never tempted into a last-minute crash. And since a sanctioned weigh-in is involved, have a dietitian or an experienced coach sanity-check the final stretch — that's where cuts usually go wrong.",
